name: Biden speech
summary: In his Oval Office address, President Biden announced his decision to withdraw from the 2024 presidential race, emphasizing the need to defend democracy as his primary motivation. While his speech aimed to rouse Americans to safeguard democratic principles, it faced criticism for avoiding specific challenges confronting the nation. The media highlighted key takeaways, including Biden's appeal to pass on the responsibility for upholding democratic values and his emphasis on the significance of citizen engagement in preserving the republic. Biden's decision was widely reported as a matter of principle, with analysts noting that it came at a time when American democracy faces significant challenges. The speech garnered attention for its focus on defending democratic institutions and unity amidst political divisions.

name: Humpback whale capsizes boat
summary: On the coast of New Hampshire, a humpback whale breached the water and capsized a boat carrying three people. The boaters were thrown into the Atlantic Ocean but miraculously survived. Witnesses reported that the whale may have been agitated due to fishing activity in the area. Captivating video captured by a teenager shows the whale surfacing and striking the boat, causing it to overturn. Officials speculate that the whale may have been startled or disoriented by the boat's sudden movement. The boaters expressed gratitude for their survival and urged caution when encountering whales in their habitat.

name: Coco Gauff
summary: American tennis star Coco Gauff, at just 20 years old, will carry the U.S. flag as the female flag bearer during the 2023 Olympic Games opening ceremony. Gauff will join basketball icon LeBron James, who will serve as the male flag bearer. This marks the first time in Olympic history that the U.S. flag-bearing duties will be shared by a man and a woman. Gauff's selection as flag bearer is a testament to her remarkable achievements in tennis, including her recent Grand Slam success and her status as a role model for young athletes.
